        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Counts as Toil in a Claude Integration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Toil is manual, repetitive, automatable operational work that scales linearly with traffic or incidents and produces no permanent improvement to the system. Google SRE defined it; the concept applies directly to teams running Claude-powered services."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Toil is not just unpleasant work. It has a specific definition: manual + repetitive + automatable + scales with service growth + no lasting value. If work is manual but complex (post-mortem analysis), it is not toil. If it is repetitive but produces a lasting improvement (writing a new alert rule), it is not toil."
          }
        ]
      },
