        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Phase 1: Identifying and Measuring Toil"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You cannot reduce toil you have not measured. The identification phase creates a tracking mechanism so toil hours are visible alongside engineering hours."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tagging Tickets as Toil"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The easiest starting point is adding a toil label to any Jira/GitHub issue that represents a manual operational task. At the end of each week, pull the sum of time logged against toil-labelled issues."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# GitHub CLI: list all issues labelled 'toil' closed this month\ngh issue list --label toil --state closed \\\n  --json number,title,closedAt,timeTracked \\\n  | jq '[.[] | select(.closedAt >= \"2026-07-01\")] | length'\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "On-Call Log Annotation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Ask on-call engineers to annotate each handoff note with a count of toil events: manual restarts, queue purges, alert investigations that found nothing. Even rough counts, logged weekly, reveal trends."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "markdown"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# On-Call Handoff \u2014 Week of 2026-07-14\n\n## Toil Events This Week\n| Event                          | Count | ~Minutes Each | Total |\n|-------------------------------|-------|---------------|-------|\n| Worker restart (quota exhaust) | 3     | 5 min         | 15 min |\n| Queue purge (stale jobs)       | 2     | 10 min        | 20 min |\n| Alert investigation (no issue) | 7     | 8 min         | 56 min |\n| Manual API key check           | 1     | 15 min        | 15 min |\n\n**Total toil this week:** ~106 min (~2.5% of on-call hours)\n\n## Automation Opportunities Noted\n- Alert threshold for `claude_latency_p99` fires during batch jobs; add time window exclusion\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Phase 2: Prioritising Reduction Efforts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Not all toil is worth automating. Automation has a cost, and some toil is rare enough that scripting it would take longer than doing it manually for a year. Prioritise by ROI."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ToilItem:\n    name: str\n    hours_per_month: float       # measured from ticket logs\n    frequency_per_month: int     # how many times it occurs\n    automation_effort_hours: float  # one-time cost to automate\n    risk_if_not_automated: str   # \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\"\n\n    @property\n    def payback_months(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Months until automation effort is recouped.\"\"\"\n        if self.hours_per_month == 0:\n            return float(\"inf\")\n        return self.automation_effort_hours / self.hours_per_month\n\n    @property\n    def roi_score(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Higher = automate sooner. Frequency * hours / effort.\"\"\"\n        if self.automation_effort_hours == 0:\n            return float(\"inf\")\n        return (self.frequency_per_month * self.hours_per_month) / self.automation_effort_hours\n\n\nTOIL_BACKLOG = [\n    ToilItem(\"Worker restart after quota exhaustion\", 0.25, 3, 8.0, \"medium\"),\n    ToilItem(\"Queue purge of stale jobs\", 0.33, 2, 4.0, \"low\"),\n    ToilItem(\"Alert noise triage\", 0.93, 7, 12.0, \"low\"),\n    ToilItem(\"Prompt template prod push\", 0.50, 4, 20.0, \"high\"),\n    ToilItem(\"API key rotation\", 0.25, 1, 6.0, \"high\"),\n]\n\n# Sort by ROI score (descending) for backlog prioritisation\nfor item in sorted(TOIL_BACKLOG, key=lambda x: x.roi_score, reverse=True):\n    print(f\"{item.name}: ROI={item.roi_score:.2f}, payback={item.payback_months:.1f} months\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Items with payback_months < 3 and risk_if_not_automated == 'high' should go directly to the next sprint regardless of ROI score. API key rotation is a security risk, not just an efficiency problem."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Phase 3: Automation Patterns for Common Claude Toil"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automatic Worker Recovery from Quota Exhaustion"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Kubernetes liveness probe + quota-aware restart\n# workers/health.py\nimport os\nimport asyncio\nimport anthropic\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\n\napp = FastAPI()\nclient = anthropic.AsyncAnthropic(api_key=os.environ[\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"])\n\n_quota_exhausted = False\n\n\nasync def _quota_watchdog() -> None:\n    \"\"\"Probe Claude API every 60 s; set flag on 429 with no Retry-After.\"\"\"\n    global _quota_exhausted\n    while True:\n        try:\n            await client.messages.create(\n                model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                max_tokens=1,\n                messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"ping\"}],\n            )\n            _quota_exhausted = False\n        except anthropic.RateLimitError as e:\n            retry_after = e.response.headers.get(\"retry-after\")\n            if retry_after is None:\n                _quota_exhausted = True   # daily quota, not rate limit\n        await asyncio.sleep(60)\n\n\n@app.on_event(\"startup\")\nasync def startup():\n    asyncio.create_task(_quota_watchdog())\n\n\n@app.get(\"/healthz/live\")\nasync def liveness():\n    # Kubernetes kills the pod if this returns non-200\n    if _quota_exhausted:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=503, detail=\"quota exhausted\")\n    return {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dead-Letter Queue for Stale Jobs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# sqs_worker.py \u2014 move jobs older than 24 h to DLQ automatically\nimport boto3\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta\n\nsqs = boto3.client(\"sqs\", region_name=\"us-east-1\")\nQUEUE_URL = os.environ[\"CLAUDE_JOB_QUEUE_URL\"]\nDLQ_URL = os.environ[\"CLAUDE_JOB_DLQ_URL\"]\nMAX_AGE = timedelta(hours=24)\n\n\ndef reap_stale_jobs() -> int:\n    \"\"\"Move jobs older than MAX_AGE to DLQ. Returns count moved.\"\"\"\n    moved = 0\n    while True:\n        resp = sqs.receive_message(\n            QueueUrl=QUEUE_URL,\n            MaxNumberOfMessages=10,\n            MessageAttributeNames=[\"All\"],\n            VisibilityTimeout=30,\n        )\n        messages = resp.get(\"Messages\", [])\n        if not messages:\n            break\n        for msg in messages:\n            enqueued_at_str = msg[\"MessageAttributes\"].get(\"EnqueuedAt\", {}).get(\"StringValue\")\n            if enqueued_at_str:\n                enqueued_at = datetime.fromisoformat(enqueued_at_str)\n                if datetime.now(timezone.utc) - enqueued_at > MAX_AGE:\n                    sqs.send_message(QueueUrl=DLQ_URL, MessageBody=msg[\"Body\"])\n                    sqs.delete_message(QueueUrl=QUEUE_URL, ReceiptHandle=msg[\"ReceiptHandle\"])\n                    moved += 1\n                    continue\n            # Release visibility for non-stale messages\n            sqs.change_message_visibility(\n                QueueUrl=QUEUE_URL,\n                ReceiptHandle=msg[\"ReceiptHandle\"],\n                VisibilityTimeout=0,\n            )\n    return moved\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automated API Key Rotation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/bin/bash\n# rotate-anthropic-key.sh \u2014 rotate Anthropic API key in AWS Secrets Manager\n# Run via EventBridge on a 90-day schedule\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\nSECRET_NAME=\"${ANTHROPIC_KEY_SECRET_NAME:-anthropic/api-key}\"\nNEW_KEY=\"${NEW_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY}\"  # injected by rotation Lambda\n\n# 1. Update the secret value\naws secretsmanager put-secret-value \\\n  --secret-id \"${SECRET_NAME}\" \\\n  --secret-string \"{\"api_key\": \"${NEW_KEY}\"}\"\n\n# 2. Trigger rolling restart so workers pick up the new key\nkubectl rollout restart deployment/claude-worker\n\n# 3. Wait for rollout to complete\nkubectl rollout status deployment/claude-worker --timeout=120s\n\necho \"Key rotation complete for ${SECRET_NAME}\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
