      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Measuring Program Health"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Track two numbers at the monthly reliability review to monitor the health of the toil reduction program:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Total toil hours per month (absolute). This should trend downward as automation matures. If it stays flat while traffic grows, toil is actually growing as a fraction of operational capacity."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Toil as a percentage of total on-call hours. The SRE target is below 50%; teams with a healthy automation backlog trend toward 30% or below."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ToilMetrics:\n    month: str\n    total_oncall_hours: float\n    toil_hours: float\n\n    @property\n    def toil_pct(self) -> float:\n        return self.toil_hours / self.total_oncall_hours if self.total_oncall_hours else 0.0\n\n    @property\n    def status(self) -> str:\n        if self.toil_pct < 0.30:\n            return \"green\"\n        if self.toil_pct < 0.50:\n            return \"yellow\"\n        return \"red\"\n\n\nHISTORY = [\n    ToilMetrics(\"2026-04\", 80, 48),   # 60% \u2014 red\n    ToilMetrics(\"2026-05\", 82, 42),   # 51% \u2014 red\n    ToilMetrics(\"2026-06\", 84, 38),   # 45% \u2014 yellow\n    ToilMetrics(\"2026-07\", 86, 30),   # 35% \u2014 yellow (improving)\n]\n\nfor m in HISTORY:\n    print(f\"{m.month}: {m.toil_pct:.0%} ({m.status}) \u2014 {m.toil_hours:.0f} h toil / {m.total_oncall_hours:.0f} h total\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Toil reduction is a program, not a sprint. It requires a measurement system, a prioritised backlog, deployed automation, and ongoing verification \u2014 not a one-time cleanup."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Classify toil by the SRE definition: manual, repetitive, automatable, scales with service growth, no lasting value. Do not confuse toil with complex or important work."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Measure toil by tagging tickets and annotating on-call handoffs with event counts. Rough data collected consistently beats precise data collected never."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prioritise the toil backlog by ROI score (frequency \u00d7 hours \u00f7 automation effort). Fast-track high-risk items (key rotation, security-adjacent) regardless of ROI."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Automate common Claude integration toil: quota exhaustion recovery via liveness probes, stale job reaping via DLQ TTL, API key rotation via Secrets Manager."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Verify automation by checking on-call logs for 4 consecutive weeks with zero manual occurrences before retiring the item."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Report total toil hours and toil percentage at the monthly reliability review. Target: below 50%; healthy target: 30%."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
